Holograph is based on Propagator Networks, who were discovered and written about by Gerald Sussman and Alexey Radul. They described "a flexible and expressive substrate for computation". Each propagator ideally is an independently machine. It's effectively a massively parallel and distributable computational system, and it just so happens to power visual systems beautifully.
